1. Enable cilium in your k8s cluster:
   - git config --global --add safe.directory /snap/microk8s/current/addons/community/.git
   - microk8s enable community
   - microk8s enable cilium
   - sudo microk8s cilium hubble enable
   - microk8s cilium status
   - microk8s cilium version
   - microk8s kubectl get pods --all-namespaces

2. Observe traffic flows within the cilium agent pod
   - microk8s kubectl -n kube-system exec cilium-92mjm -it -- hubble observe

3. Observe that the database pod is ping-able
   - microk8s kubectl exec backend-667b84d68d-mflfl -- curl -s database/PING

4. Enable ingress-only policy on database pod
   - microk8s kubectl apply -f database-ingress-only-policy.yml 


